Telegram Speed Downloader Bot
=============================

Speed Downloader Bot is a high-performance Telegram bot designed for fast file
downloads from Telegram messages. Built with Pyrogram/Hydrogram, it features
optimized concurrent transmissions and a comprehensive file management system
with an intuitive keyboard-based interface.


Quick start
-----------

Report a bug: See Documentation/reporting-issues.rst
Join the community: https://t.me/aliendevlab


What it does
------------

Speed Downloader Bot listens for incoming files, videos, and audio messages on
Telegram and downloads them instantly to a local directory. It provides a full
set of file management tools through an interactive button menu.

Supported media types:

* Documents (any file type)
* Videos (MP4, MKV, AVI, etc.)
* Audio files (MP3, FLAC, WAV, etc.)

The bot also includes:

* Persistent keyboard menu for easy navigation
* File listing with size information
* Selective deletion (files only or everything)
* File organization (move to dated folders)
* Storage status monitoring


Why it exists
-------------

Manually downloading files from Telegram using a desktop client is slow and
lacks automation. Many users need a dedicated bot that:

* Downloads files without size limitations (unlike web clients)
* Maintains an organized local archive
* Provides batch file management capabilities
* Runs unattended on a server or VPS

Speed Downloader Bot exists to solve these problems with a focus on speed,
reliability, and ease of use.


Core features
-------------

* High-speed downloads – Configurable concurrent transmissions (default: 12)
* Persistent keyboard menu – All actions available via buttons
* File listing – View all downloaded files with human-readable sizes
* Selective deletion – Delete files only OR delete everything (including folders)
* Batch move – Organize files into auto-named dated folders
* Storage status – Total files, folders, size, and free disk space
* Multi-format support – Documents, videos, audio files
* Error handling – Graceful fallbacks for permission issues
* Session persistence – Bot resumes downloads after restart


System requirements
-------------------

* Python 3.8 or higher (3.14 recommended)
* Telegram API credentials (API ID, API Hash, Bot Token)
* Sufficient disk space for downloaded content
* Internet connection (for Telegram API)

Python dependencies:
* hydrogram (Pyrogram-based)
* No other external libraries required


Installation
------------

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/AK-ALiEN/telegram-speed-downloader.git
   cd telegram-speed-downloader

2. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run the bot for the first time:
   python main.py

4. Enter your Telegram credentials when prompted:
   * API_ID (from my.telegram.org)
   * API_HASH (from my.telegram.org)
   * BOT_TOKEN (from @BotFather)
   * DOWNLOAD_DIR (optional, defaults to ./downloads/)

5. Configuration is saved to config.json for future runs.


How to use
----------

Start the bot on Telegram with /start command.

The main menu provides these buttons:

📁 View Files        – List all downloaded files and folders
🗑️ Delete Files      – Show delete options submenu
📦 Move Files        – Move all files to a dated folder (YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS)
ℹ️ Status           – Show storage usage and bot status
❌ Delete All       – Emergency delete of everything

Delete submenu:
* Delete Files Only – Remove files, keep folders
* Delete All (Including Folders) – Complete wipe
* Back to Main Menu

To download a file:
1. Simply send any document, video, or audio to the bot
2. The bot will acknowledge and start downloading immediately
3. Upon completion, it reports the save location and total time


Configuration
-------------

The bot creates a config.json file on first run:

{
    "API_ID": 123456,
    "API_HASH": "your_api_hash_here",
    "BOT_TOKEN": "your_bot_token_here",
    "DOWNLOAD_DIR": "./downloads/"
}

You can edit this file directly to change settings without re-prompting.

Performance tuning (in main.py):
* max_concurrent_transmissions – Parallel downloads (default: 12)
* workers – Thread pool size (default: 20)


File management details
-----------------------

Download directory structure:
downloads/
├── file1.pdf
├── video.mp4
├── 2025-01-15_14-30-22/    (created by Move Files)
│   ├── old_file.zip
│   └── another.doc
└── 2025-01-16_09-15-45/    (another move operation)

The bot excludes its own session files from deletion and move operations to
prevent interruption of service.


Design philosophy
-----------------

Speed Downloader Bot follows a few simple rules:

* Do one job well – download and manage Telegram files
* Keep the interface simple – buttons over commands
* Prioritize speed over fancy features
* Stay self-contained – no external databases
* Handle errors gracefully – never crash on permission issues


Limitations
-----------

* Telegram bot API limits file size to 2GB (server limitation)
* Requires constant internet connection
* No built-in file preview or streaming
* No support for forwarded messages with multiple media
* Session files must be preserved for uninterrupted operation


Troubleshooting
---------------

Bot asks for credentials every time?
→ Check that config.json is writable and in the same directory.

Download stuck or very slow?
→ Reduce max_concurrent_transmissions to 4-6 if on limited bandwidth.

Permission errors when deleting/moving?
→ Ensure the bot has write permissions for DOWNLOAD_DIR.

Bot doesn't respond to buttons?
→ Start a new conversation with /start to reset the menu state.

Session expired errors?
→ Delete the .session files and restart. New login will be required.


Security & Responsibility
-------------------------

This bot is intended for:

* Personal file backup and organization
* Automated downloading from your own Telegram channels
* Legitimate file management tasks

Security notes:

* API credentials are stored in plain text JSON – protect this file
* The bot does not share or transmit your files anywhere
* All processing happens locally on your machine

You are responsible for:

* The security of your API credentials
* Compliance with Telegram Terms of Service
* Files you choose to download

Do not use this bot for downloading copyrighted or unauthorized content.


Commands reference
------------------

/start      – Initialize bot and show main menu
(No other commands – everything is button-driven)


